We random and it works flawlessly.  But then we engineered the guild to be that way.  We hated people bickering over loot and such, so we only invite people we like, and who like us, into the guild.  New people come in slowly and in small numbers so we don't have a big influx of alternate loot ideas.  <br>
<br>
We have very few rules.  People who can and will use get frist shot.  If there are none of them we random for cashloot or let it rot (or loot for mq).  Everyone who can use gets to roll, but people often pass if they feel it is important for someone else to have it.  <br>
<br>
I hear alot of people say random isn't fair as it gives someone who raids infrequently the same chance to get an item as someone who raids almost every time, but that just isn't true.  They have the same odds as you for that one raid, but there were there just as much as you for that one raid.  They have lower odds overall, if they attend fewer raids overall.  <br>
<br>
But yeah for a guild that is anything other than a friend based guild you will have issues with random, as people will get jealous when they are on the bad side of the random.  If the other officers ever want to open up recruitment in our guild I  will be requiring them to switch to a point system first (partially pressure to keep the guild small :P) to avoid these arguements.  <br>
<br>
Anyway ... more to the point ... I am MA on 95% or more of our raids, and I don't feel that I should get merits.  Most places we go don't actually have any upgrades for me anyway (we arent very uber) but when I something I could use does drop I expected others to roll.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=252504" target="top">Xath Carnage</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raunstoncutter>RaunStoncutter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 360<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/26/03 4:23 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/raunstonecutter/bunnyhop.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Random = suckage</span><hr size=1> I'm personally against randoms.  I would prefer merit or DKP.  My guild randoms 90% of our stuff (which is ok some of the times), and certain items get merited.  While I disagree with our loot system, it's not too horrible, certanily better than full equiping a MT than everyone else.<br>
<br>
Don't worry about the 41% haste neck, I hear it is a common drop.  As far as merit goes, I got my first raid loot merit item just recently, and I've been in my guild for what feels like forever.  Its important to make sure everyone gets a shot at gear.  Its sure nice to have someone decked out, but like Surlok said, it can be problematic.<br>
<br>
If you like your guild, you can suck it up and deal with the loot system.  Or if it does really upset you that much, there are plenty of other guild around as well. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=31658">Raun Stonecutter</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.swordoffate.com">&lt;Sword of Fate&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
