<br>
So long as the only goal is to hang together and have a bit of fun, Random is good. There is no overhead involved, and if people really do fit within the 'family' theme of the guild they won't be rolling on stuff they don't actually need. My prevous guild was this type and it worked well for us for a long time.<br>
<br>
If Raiding is a major reason for your guilds existance, then it doesn't work long-term for all the reasons already mentioned. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:medium;">Zyphyr Runnersbane</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
