Tis the way my guild currently works it.  Other rare drops are also awarded.  Most officer-decided loot are usually based off a database (who has attended what raids, what has been merited, etc).  Most may be private (officers' eyes only), some may post the info.<br>
<br>
As for EToV, it really doesnt need to be a raid adventure either, esp with the raid feature.<br>
<br>
Basically, the very important pieces should be merited out, if at all possible.  But it requires communication on all fronts. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27263">Baron Sarkaukar Halfear</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Warder, 1st Tier<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Utopian</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shikariiapoccalypse>Shikarii Apoccalypse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>All in the reflexes</BR>Guardian of the Bunker</BR>STEEL WARRIOR Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 2458<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/03 4:11 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How does your guild equip the MA warrior?</span><hr size=1> no matter what way you skin a cat; the cat will get pissed.<br>
<br>
DKP, Loot Council, Random, Pay, Ninja, etc...whatever. no matter how you distribute something of monetary or essential worth someone <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>will</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> be upset about it. Myself, I was a member of my guilds former Loot Council and we tried to keep a pretty even keel on keeping the classes up to snuff with each other; than realised when the guild went over 100 members; that DKP was the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>only</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> way to go. DKP distributes itself; you raid you can get loot. You don't raid and don't get DKP, well, you're just not there enough and can't get the l33t items.<br>
<br>
These days i barely even log on; and so far i've got decent enough upgrades on gear and i just let the big time raiders get the better of the drops because; well, they've earned it more than I did. No fuss; no worries; and nothing I can do but Raid More. <br>
<br>
Honestly, look into DKP more if you're looking for fair loot distribution with the least amount of human emotional interference. DKP just needs numbers put into it and the rest governs itself. and it's a great way to finally put the nail in the coffin if you're looking for a reason to retire. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=458241">My Sanford &amp; Son Starter Set</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimmlokk>Grimmlokk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 1095<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/03 7:39 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/spinhead2.gif?flezbwidth=30&flezbheight=41? WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How does your guild equip the MA warrior?</span><hr size=1>  Buncha random tidbits.<br>
<br>
 Merit/Officer award works much better if you really track as much as possible. One of our officers has built us a huge database for our people. We track every item dropped. Used to mostly go by what was written in various notebooks and memory. It was iffy sometimes. Works great now I think. Much less room for error.<br>
<br>
 One of the guilds on my server has an...interesting take on random. They earn points and when an item drops they want they bid an amoutn of points. More points they bid the higher number they get to random from. Or for. @#%$ if I know. But it's basically a weighted random system. Seems a bit odd for a fairly high end raiding guild, but apparently works for them.<br>
<br>
 Of the 6-7 higher end raiding bodies on our server(near VT+ at least). We use the merit one listed above, seems to work better for our friendly, more casual brand of high end raiding alliance(hey we're in Ele Planes, must be doing something right=P). Everyone else uses DKP of some sort. Top 2 FR killing guilds full normal DKP. 1 uses that random contraption I mentioned. And the &quot;public&quot; uses DKP too. Hey the Public does everything up to Agnarr=P<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wulfran>wulfran</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/03 9:17 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   We use a modified loot council...</span><hr size=1> Our awards are mostly merit.<br>
<br>
Our awarding council is 3 officers and 4 random members (ie 1 wis caster, 1 int caster, 1 DPS, 1 tank). People interested seend tells to a designated spokesperson, and they indicate what they are replacing and how bad they want it (hi, med or low interest).<br>
<br>
Decisions are based on time in guild, raid attendance, degree of upgrade, etc.<br>
<br>
As an MT who tries to be there as much as possible this has worked well for me. There are people who don't like it, but thats their right, as is the right to move on. I'm not saying I agree with every award, but you have to take the view that your raid force is improving with every drop, and as the raid force improves so will the number and quality of drops.<br>
<br>
It doesn't matter what you use, a system like ours (merit/council), DKP, or random someone will always be unhappy because they think more about themselves than the raid force. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hulanta>Hulanta</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 179<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/03 10:12 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: We use a modified loot council...</span><hr size=1> Very simple:<br>
<br>
If you don't agree with the method that your guild rewards its players, join a guild where you do agree.  (For each kind of loot system, there are people who think it is the best or fairest.  Find like minded people.) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lling>Lling</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/03 12:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: We use a modified loot council...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I'm not saying I agree with every award, but you have to take the view that your raid force is improving with every drop, and as the raid force improves so will the number and quality of drops.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
*nod* That is looking at the big picture and not the short-term gratification.<br>
<br>
And if you don't like your current system, there are other options besides finding another guild. I cannot even visualize doing that. I love my guild so much that if someone even utters a minor complaint about our system I get defensive and protective. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
If you don't like the system, but you like your guild, ask about changing it. You don't accomplish anything by leaving. You could accomplish a lot by working out a system. Don't just say &quot;I don't like this - let's change it!&quot; Come up with a plan. Try to make it fair and reasonable. It's amazing what communication can accomplish. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
