Right now we're in our 2nd yr of real raiding and our system of randoming most drops w/ lvl and class restrictions and occasional defaulting has worked fairly well. Sure there is grumbling when someone comes to their 1st raid in weeks and wins something or joins up and wins something soon after. That is why we have put more and more restrictions on loot rolls and instituted probationary periods after someone joins guild or decides to flip out and complain constantly about loot. Of course whenever we add more restrictions the officers tend to take a lot of heat for it and are accused of some sort of conspiracy BS and favoritism to equip only certain ppl. You saw this the other day when I refused to let Rug roll on a driver a day or 2 after hitting 60, I got to read all sorts of flames regarding that from him and hook. Oh well, I didnt choose to accept the officer job because I wanted to make friends, I just wanted to be able to lead more raids (I was very stupid at the time I accepted). Whining over loot rules by a small portion of the guild has always and will always be present. These ppl overall don't last long and we move on to bigger and better things and leave them behind.<br>
